@node "Description" "Description"

@{jcenter}
@{b}Disciption@{ub}@{line}
@{line}
With this tool, you can restore files on PFS3 and PFS2 formated drives. @{line}
@{line}
Simple doubleclick the device to get the .deldir list of this device. Doubleclick the files you want to restore.@{line}
If you have selected all files you want to restore, so click on the Restore button and you'll find all files in the selected Destination.@{line}
If you did a mistake, just doubleclick the file in the List to remove it.@{line}
In the Direct Mode, the files are directly on selection restored.@{line}

@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"

@{b}Installation@{ub}@{line}
@{line}
Install the program wherever you want.@{line}

@endnode

@node "Problems" "Problems"

@{b}Problems@{ub}@{line}
@{line}
@{b}1@{ub}@{line}
If you have the PFS3 standartversion installed (TD64) and have a larg deldir list or larg files in the deldir list, your machine sometimes lockup.@{line}
This is not an error of my program, it is an error from PFS3 (TD64).@{line}
I have tried to salv the problem and I have found a way:@{line}
Just install the PFS3ds (direct scsi) version and all works fine!@{line}
@{line}
@{b}2@{ub}@{line}
If you have larg deldir list or larg files in the deldir list, the reading take time. Thats normal.@{line}
Also to undelete a big file needs some time.@{line}
@{line}

@endnode

@node "FAQ" "FAQ"

@{u}FAQ@{uu}@{line}
@{line}
@{b}Q: Why is the Blocksnumber 0?@{ub}@{line}
A: Firts you have to get the setdeldir-exe in the PFS3ud.@{line}
@{line}
@{b}Q: I've graphical errors in the Lists!@{ub}@{line}
A: You're using an unproportional font. Use proportional fonts.@{line}
@{line}
@{b}Q: The window looks different between PFS2/PFS3 and DirectMode. Is this normal?@{ub}@{line}
A: Yes. Unsupported tools in PFS2- and DirectMode are removed. @{line}
@{line}

@endnode

@node "Menu" "Menu"

@{b}Menu@{ub}@{line}
@{line}
  Project@{line}
    About@{line}
      Prints information abou the program.@{line}
@{line}
  Project@{line}
    Quit@{line}
      Quit the program.@{line}
@{line}
@{line}
  Use@{line}
    Set Deldir@{line}
      Open a Requester to set the deldirblocks of a device.@{line}
@{line}
  Use@{line}
    Clear Deldir@{line}
      Remove all files from .deldir list.@{line}
@{line}
  Use@{line}
    Get setdeldir@{line}
      Get the setdeldir-exe.@{line}
@{line}
  Use@{line}
    Get Source@{line}
      Read the Sourcedevices.@{line}
@{line}
  Use@{line}
    Get Destination@{line}
      Read the Destinationlist.@{line}
@{line}
  Use@{line}
    Get .deldir@{line}
      Get the deldir list of the selected device in the Source list.@{line}
@{line}
  Use@{line}
    Restore@{line}
      Restore the Files from the List in the selected device from the destination list.@{line}
@{line}
@{line}
  Settings@{line}
    Remove Number@{line}
      If selected all numbers from PFS3 are removed from the filename.@{line}
@{line}
  Settings@{line}
    No Multiselect@{line}
      If aktivated, you can't select the same file several times.@{line}
@{line}
  Settings@{line}
    PFS Detection@{line}
      If enabled only PFS devices with a .deldir list are shown in the source list.@{line}
@{line}
  Settings@{line}
    Direct Mode@{line}
      If enabled, all doubleclicket files are restored immediately. @{line}
@{line}
  Settings@{line}
    PFS Mode@{line}
      Select the operationmode of PFS3ud. Select the right one of your PFS Version (PFS2 or PFS3).@{line}
@{line}
  Settings@{line}
    Sort by:@{line}
      List the .deldir/ list sorted by name or by age.@{line}
@{line}
  Settings@{line}
    Load Settings@{line}
      Load the settings.@{line}
@{line}
  Settings@{line}
    Save Settings@{line}
      Save the settings.@{line}

@endnode

@node "Special" "Special"

@{b}Special:@{ub}@{line}
@{line}
Restoring of a full .deldir list of a device:@{line}
Keep the list of the files to undelet clear and press Restore. After this, all files of the selected Source device are restored in the Destination device.@{line}

@endnode

